<item>

	<title>phobos: Updated guide to blogging anonymously</title>
	<dcterms:creator>phobos</dcterms:creator>


	<guid>http://localhost/jmtodaro/tor/blog/posts/Updated_guide_to_blogging_anonymously/</guid>

	<link>http://localhost/jmtodaro/tor/blog/posts/Updated_guide_to_blogging_anonymously/</link>


	<category>/tags/anonymity_advocacy</category>

	<category>/tags/anonymous_publishing</category>

	<category>/tags/global_voices</category>


	<pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2009 19:58:05 -0500</pubDate>
	<dcterms:modified>2011-04-05T11:20:50Z</dcterms:modified>

	<description>&lt;p&gt;We worked with Sami from Global Voices to update their &lt;a href=&quot;http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/projects/guide/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;guide to blogging anonymously&lt;/a&gt;.  The big changes are more screenshots, easier instructions, and suggested use of the Tor Browser Bundle by default; as it&#39;s generaly plug and play.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Citizen Media Law Project also has a good &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/how-maintain-your-anonymity-online&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;guide to anonymity online&lt;/a&gt;.  Be sure to check out the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/potential-legal-challenges-anonymity&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;legal challenges to anonymity online&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/legal-protections-anonymous-speech&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;legal protections to anonymous speech&lt;/a&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>


